so much larger on this side?

487
00:38:31,503 --> 00:38:34,187
All the better to see you with,
my dear.

488
00:38:35,663 --> 00:38:38,477
At the greatest possible angle.

489
00:39:03,100 --> 00:39:04,757
And cut!

490
00:39:23,153 --> 00:39:25,231
If you ask me, the credits should read

491
00:39:25,254 --> 00:39:29,338
"Screenplay by Joseph Stefano
and Alma Reville."

492
00:39:29,361 --> 00:39:31,840
The people who matter know.

493
00:39:37,003 --> 00:39:40,340
Alma, you always know the answer.
Is this really going to work?

494
00:39:46,670 --> 00:39:48,953
See you tomorrow.

495
00:40:02,480 --> 00:40:04,394
Hello, stranger.

496
00:40:04,418 --> 00:40:08,434
- Whit!
- Where have you been hiding?

497
00:40:08,457 --> 00:40:10,512
Oh, God...!

498
00:40:10,524 --> 00:40:13,424
- I've been finishing the revisions on...
- Psycho.

499
00:40:13,448 --> 00:40:16,160
- Mm-hmm.
- And how is the old boy?

500
00:40:16,182 --> 00:40:20,439
He is in a state of unbridled ecstasy
now that he's back on the set.

501
00:40:20,463 --> 00:40:22,517
And you? How are you?

502
00:40:23,609 --> 00:40:28,659
Well, two thousand words to do
for Reader's Digest on

503
00:40:28,683 --> 00:40:32,018
what it's like to be married to
a man obsessed by murder.

504
00:40:34,918 --> 00:40:38,578
Alma, you deserve a break.

505
00:40:39,603 --> 00:40:41,599
Let's drive up to Santa Barbara.

506
00:40:41,622 --> 00:40:45,620
We'll have Emilio fry up those juicy
steaks that we love so much at El Encanto.

507
00:40:47,214 --> 00:40:49,794
Mr. Hitchcock,
we're ready for you on the set.

508
00:40:54,096 --> 00:40:57,836
- Mr. Hitchcock.
- I'll be there in a moment.

509
00:41:21,765 --> 00:41:24,228
Long line at the supermarket?

510
00:41:27,226 --> 00:41:29,894
No. Actually,
I'm home earlier than I expected.

511
00:41:33,510 --> 00:41:38,243
- Would you like a cocktail?
- No, and you shouldn't have one either.

512
00:41:45,790 --> 00:41:49,684
- That hasn't been washed yet.
- I don't care.

513
00:41:52,645 --> 00:41:57,102
Oh, I was filming all day today
with John Gavin.

514
00:41:57,126 --> 00:41:59,529
He's a good-looking chap.

515
00:41:59,544 --> 00:42:03,017
But really, plywood is more expressive.

516
00:42:04,358 --> 00:42:06,916
I think his love scene with Janet Leigh

517
00:42:06,940 --> 00:42:10,693
may be most horrifying thing
in the movie.

518
00:42:14,333 --> 00:42:17,205
Even your friend Mr. Whitfield Cook

519
00:42:17,206 --> 00:42:19,793
would be better in the scene.

520
00:42:21,249 --> 00:42:24,528
Why don't you tell him yourself?
I'm sure he'd be very flattered.

521
00:42:35,790 --> 00:42:38,244
You know, my dear,

522
00:42:38,268 --> 00:42:43,681
maybe I was a bit too dismissive
about your friend

523
00:42:43,698 --> 00:42:46,688
Whitfield's book.

524
00:42:47,885 --> 00:42:53,232
Perhaps he and Elizabeth
could come over this weekend

525
00:42:53,255 --> 00:42:55,755
and walk me through it, as they say.

526
00:42:57,790 --> 00:43:00,654
Lovely woman, Elizabeth.

527
00:43:04,291 --> 00:43:09,054
I was hoping you could
come to the set tomorrow.

528
00:43:10,591 --> 00:43:14,012
Yes. Well,
I'll see how my day shapes up.

529
00:43:15,002 --> 00:43:17,035
Yes.

530
00:43:22,358 --> 00:43:26,491
You think you can get away with it,
don't you? But you can't.

531
00:43:26,515 --> 00:43:29,229
You think they can't tell,
but they can.

532
00:43:29,253 --> 00:43:31,162
They know.

533
00:43:31,186 --> 00:43:35,988
You can feel that noose tightening
around that breakable little neck.

534
00:43:36,006 --> 00:43:37,993
I mean,
you could return the money secretly,

535
00:43:38,017 --> 00:43:40,165
but what would that prove?
It's too late.

536
00:43:40,189 --> 00:43:42,999
Marion Crane always so tight,
so respectable,

537
00:43:43,023 --> 00:43:46,713
so prim and so proper and perfect.
Untouchable unsullied Miss Crane.

538
00:43:46,737 --> 00:43:49,107
Daddy's perfect little angel.

539
00:43:49,130 --> 00:43:54,080
Now they all know those dirty
little secrets you've been hiding so long.

540
00:43:54,102 --> 00:43:56,151
Messy, sticky little lunchtime trysts

541
00:43:56,175 --> 00:44:00,458
with that oh-so-handsome failure
Mr. Samuel Loomis.

542
00:44:00,481 --> 00:44:02,823
They'll smirk, they'll gossip,
and they'll whisper.

543
00:44:02,846 --> 00:44:06,333
Even your boss, straight-laced,
hatchet-faced Mr. George Lowery,

544
00:44:06,357 --> 00:44:11,538
why even he can smell the rancid,
pungent scent of sex all over you.

545
00:44:12,880 --> 00:44:14,750
All right. Circle that and print it.

546
00:44:14,768 --> 00:44:16,905
Let's get this thing fixed
once and for all.

547
00:44:16,928 --> 00:44:19,277
I'm sick and tired of it.
Come on.

548
00:44:21,145 --> 00:44:23,199
Why's it making that noise?

549
00:44:23,223 --> 00:44:26,992
- What's it going to take to reset?
- About five.

550
00:44:34,770 --> 00:44:36,308
Come in.

551
00:44:37,858 --> 00:44:40,417
Thought you could use a little
pick-me-up.

552
00:44:40,441 --> 00:44:42,921
- Oh, you're so sweet. Thank you.
- Not at all.

553
00:44:42,944 --> 00:44:45,707
- Here, have a seat.
- Thanks.

554
00:44:45,730 --> 00:44:49,546
I can't imagine your husband will be
too pleased with what just happened.

555
00:44:49,563 --> 00:44:52,017
Well, you know.

556
00:44:52,040 --> 00:44:55,248
Tony and the kids, you'd be surprised
what comes out of their mouths sometimes.

557
00:44:55,259 --> 00:44:57,370
That's true.

558
00:44:58,207 --> 00:45:00,890
You haven't spoken to him
much about your personal life, have you?

559
00:45:01,525 --> 00:45:04,475
Hitch?
No, not really.

560
00:45:06,349 --> 00:45:08,107
I'd keep it that way if I were you.

561
00:45:12,766 --> 00:45:13,950
Why?

562
00:45:14,878 --> 00:45:17,553
Well, it starts with him
wanting to choose your hairstyle.

563
00:45:17,567 --> 00:45:19,539
Then he wants to choose your clothes,

564
00:45:19,563 --> 00:45:22,917
and your friends,
and how many children you should have.

565
00:45:24,056 --> 00:45:29,084
You know that poor, tortured soul
Jimmy Stewart played in Vertigo?

566
00:45:29,108 --> 00:45:31,503
That's Hitch...

567
00:45:31,526 --> 00:45:34,091
Only younger,
slimmer and better-looking.

568
00:45:34,115 --> 00:45:36,275
Oh, I don't know.

569
00:45:36,299 --> 00:45:38,577
Compared to Orson Welles,
he's a sweetheart.

570
00:45:46,480 --> 00:45:50,403
See?
He's always watching.

571
00:46:30,415 --> 00:46:33,609
- Jack, how long is this going to take?
- Just need five minutes.

572
00:46:33,632 --> 00:46:35,673
Let's get a move on it.
We haven't got all day.

573
00:46:35,685 --> 00:46:38,139
Why does it keep
burning out all the time?

574
00:46:38,151 --> 00:46:42,070
- Get it fixed. What's the hold-up?
- It's still engaged.

575
00:46:43,092 --> 00:46:45,823
Hitch, I'm stuck on Lila's first scene.

576
00:46:45,846 --> 00:46:48,260
I don't know how strongly
I should confront Sam and the detective...

577
00:46:48,283 --> 00:46:52,316
Darling, just fake it. Fake it.
You know how to do that. Act.

578
00:46:52,340 --> 00:46:54,618
Where are my revisions?

579
00:46:57,163 --> 00:47:00,666
Come on, does it really require
two men to carry a light stand?

580
00:47:00,689 --> 00:47:01,969
Help them.

581
00:47:01,970 --> 00:47:03,249
I'll take care of it
right away, Mr. Hitchcock.

582
00:47:03,270 --> 00:47:06,099
All the difference when the money's
coming out of your own pocket, isn't it?

583
00:47:06,100 --> 00:47:07,992
- We'll have a late lunch.
- Right.

584
00:47:08,016 --> 00:47:11,620
- I'll make the reservation for 1:30.
- Oh, Whit.

585
00:47:11,644 --> 00:47:14,036
What would I do without you?

586
00:47:14,402 --> 00:47:17,733
- Till then, bye-bye.
- Bye.

587
00:47:25,481 --> 00:47:28,136
Whit, what did you forget now?

588
00:47:30,049 --> 00:47:31,387
Whit?

589
00:47:35,826 --> 00:47:37,229
Whit?

590
00:47:59,739 --> 00:48:01,510
- Mr. Hitchcock, sir, please...
- No, not now.

591
00:48:01,511 --> 00:48:03,159
Every press outlet is dying for photos.

592
00:48:03,160 --> 00:48:04,761
If we could just get one photo, please!

593
00:48:04,762 --> 00:48:07,647
Get off my set! I'll have security...
Get off my set!

594
00:48:07,670 --> 00:48:09,844
Just go! Get rid of this man.
He's a bloody pest.

595
00:48:09,867 --> 00:48:11,800
Get him off the set now!

596
00:48:11,823 --> 00:48:14,263
- Are you okay? You've gone very pale.
- I tell you get away.

597
00:48:14,287 --> 00:48:16,914
Stop following me around
like a puppy dog and get me a drink.

598
00:48:16,938 --> 00:48:20,098
- It's not even 3:00...
- Now give me the key to the cabinets.

599
00:48:23,823 --> 00:48:27,357
Hello, Hitch.
How's the picture?

600
00:48:27,380 --> 00:48:29,165
I'm hearing interesting things.

601
00:48:29,189 --> 00:48:31,220
It's a miracle anyone can hear anything

602
00:48:31,244 --> 00:48:34,340
above the noise coming from
Geoffrey Shurlock's office.

603
00:48:34,364 --> 00:48:37,569
You know, I shouldn't be in a position of
just hearing things, Hitch.

604
00:48:37,593 --> 00:48:40,814
- It's time you showed me some footage.
- Why?

605
00:48:40,838 --> 00:48:44,114
To see if you're making a picture
Paramount can actually release.

606
00:48:44,137 --> 00:48:49,117
As you well know,
my contract guarantees me final cut.

607
00:48:49,125 --> 00:48:50,954
Your contract also says

608
00:48:50,977 --> 00:48:53,255
Paramount isn't required
to distribute any film

609
00:48:53,267 --> 00:48:54,793
that could cause us embarrassment.

610
00:48:54,817 --> 00:48:58,796
Unlike the last five Martin and Lewis
films you're all so proud of.

611
00:48:58,820 --> 00:49:01,661
I demand to see some footage.
Hitch!

612
00:49:01,684 --> 00:49:05,637
You show me some damn footage now!
Hitch!

613
00:49:23,464 --> 00:49:27,230
You have no idea how wonderful it is
not to have to look after someone.

614
00:49:27,254 --> 00:49:30,436
I mean,
even if it's just for two hours.

615
00:49:30,459 --> 00:49:34,088
So where are we going, Whit?
You haven't told me.

616
00:49:34,111 --> 00:49:38,103
- I have a little surprise.
- Ooh!

617
00:49:48,339 --> 00:49:53,435
- Where's your driver?
- I've been asking myself the same thing.

618
00:49:53,459 --> 00:49:55,936
Well, I can give you a ride
if you'd like.

619
00:49:56,967 --> 00:50:00,055
Oh, my God.
What a tiny car.

620
00:50:00,078 --> 00:50:02,511
What are these things?
I keep looking at them.

621
00:50:02,512 --> 00:50:05,439
- Candy corn. The girls love them.
- Candy corn?

622
00:50:05,462 --> 00:50:08,016
I nicked them from Tony's dressing room.

623
00:50:08,027 --> 00:50:11,709
Oh. Very nice.

624
00:50:11,732 --> 00:50:14,804
I thought you only ate those
Fauchon chocolates.

625
00:50:14,818 --> 00:50:18,094
Needs must when the devil drives,
my dear.

626
00:50:19,128 --> 00:50:25,038
- Oh, luckily I'm driving.
- Thank God for that.

627
00:50:25,061 --> 00:50:27,897
He's always had obsessions
with his leading ladies.

628
00:50:27,898 --> 00:50:31,944
Just that this time it feels like
he's using them against me.

629
00:50:31,958 --> 00:50:34,499
Well I suppose
he's like any great artist.

630
00:50:34,500 --> 00:50:37,539
Impossible to live with,
but worth the effort.

631
00:50:37,562 --> 00:50:40,666
Did you know before we got together,
I was his boss?

632
00:50:40,667 --> 00:50:44,229
He had to work his way up to assistant
director before he dared ask me out.

633
00:50:44,245 --> 00:50:45,771
- Really? Huh!
- Mm-hmm.

634
00:50:51,002 --> 00:50:52,864
See that house over there?

635
00:50:54,116 --> 00:50:56,688
- Yes.
- What do you think of it?

636
00:50:56,711 --> 00:51:01,131
- Lovely, isn't it. What a great position.
- It's mine.

637
00:51:01,154 --> 00:51:03,315
I just talked to Elizabeth.
She didn't say anything about it.

638
00:51:03,338 --> 00:51:06,836
She doesn't know anything about it.
Nobody does.

639
00:51:06,859 --> 00:51:08,514
Want to see it?

640
00:51:20,697 --> 00:51:23,535
- Thank you, my dear.
- Any time.

641
00:51:23,550 --> 00:51:25,529
- Can I keep these?
- Absolutely.

642
00:51:25,553 --> 00:51:27,601
- Would you like one?
- No thank you.

643
00:51:27,622 --> 00:51:29,102
- All right. Well, thank you.
- Hitch?

644
00:51:29,125 --> 00:51:30,440
What?

645
00:51:32,002 --> 00:51:35,627
What really did happen
with you and Vera?

646
00:51:36,776 --> 00:51:39,288
Oh. Vera.

647
00:51:41,179 --> 00:51:44,805
She was going to play
the lead in Vertigo.

648
00:51:44,824 --> 00:51:49,212
Two weeks before filming
she told me was pregnant.

649
00:51:50,317 --> 00:51:53,393
I was going to make her into a star.

650
00:51:53,416 --> 00:51:57,539
But she chose
the life of a housewife instead.

651
00:52:01,642 --> 00:52:04,549
Why do they do it, I wonder?

652
00:52:05,364 --> 00:52:08,174
Why do they always betray me?

653
00:52:12,696 --> 00:52:16,212
Oh, very Bohemian.

654
00:52:16,235 --> 00:52:19,291
I just leased it for the off season.

655
00:52:19,292 --> 00:52:23,860
A place to get away from the wife,
and kids, and writing.

656
00:52:31,115 --> 00:52:34,324
Whit, I hope you don't
have the wrong idea.

657
00:52:36,121 --> 00:52:41,125
If you were serious
about helping me adapt my book,

658
00:52:41,148 --> 00:52:44,082
I thought it might make the perfect...

659
00:52:45,809 --> 00:52:47,709
hideaway.

660
00:53:00,996 --> 00:53:04,272
Relax! Naughty boys, calm down.

661
00:55:48,448 --> 00:55:51,195
Oh, by the way, I forgot to tell you

662
00:55:51,219 --> 00:55:54,503
I read your treatment of that story.

663
00:55:55,761 --> 00:55:58,428
Taxi to... Where was it, dear?

664
00:55:58,429 --> 00:56:02,052
- Dubrovnik.
- That's it. Dubrovnik.

665
00:56:05,457 --> 00:56:09,677
- Would you care to hear my opinion?
- Well, yes, naturally.

666
00:56:11,383 --> 00:56:13,102
Right, then.

667
00:56:15,013 --> 00:56:18,578
Well, my dear, there's no
other way of saying it, is there?

668
00:56:18,579 --> 00:56:20,953
It's a stillborn.

669
00:56:25,895 --> 00:56:27,703
How so?

670
00:56:27,726 --> 00:56:30,289
First of all,
the plot's a bit of a muddle, isn't it?

671
00:56:31,252 --> 00:56:33,214
Some of those jokes
are awfully like the ones

672
00:56:33,238 --> 00:56:35,646
we did so much better
hundreds of years ago

673
00:56:35,668 --> 00:56:37,918
in The Lady Vanishes.

674
00:56:37,937 --> 00:56:42,827
Also your villain is rather weak.
Well he's very weak, in fact.

675
00:56:43,882 --> 00:56:45,785
But I think the big failure

676
00:56:45,808 --> 00:56:51,443
is the relationship between
the heroine and the hero, you see.

677
00:56:54,352 --> 00:56:58,203
Probably if you weren't so smitten
with your friend Whitfield Cook,

678
00:56:58,226 --> 00:57:01,318
you'd be able to see that,
wouldn't you?

679
00:57:05,576 --> 00:57:06,668
But then I suppose

680
00:57:06,691 --> 00:57:12,345
women never really care to face the truth
when their hearts are involved, do they?

681
00:57:14,330 --> 00:57:18,229
How would you know what really goes on
between a man and a woman?

682
00:57:34,348 --> 00:57:37,177
My God, what a bloody mess.

683
00:58:28,779 --> 00:58:30,494
- No!
- Ah!

684
00:58:30,513 --> 00:58:32,796
More! More!

685
00:58:32,816 --> 00:58:34,960
- No! Oh!
- Use some guts!

686
00:58:34,977 --> 00:58:36,938
- Come on! No!
- Oh!

687
00:58:36,962 --> 00:58:40,043
- More anger!
- Oh! Oh!

688
00:58:40,066 --> 00:58:42,265
All right, cut!
Cut! Cut!

689
00:58:42,266 --> 00:58:43,737
For God's sake!

690
00:58:43,738 --> 00:58:46,460
Will someone get me
a proper stunt double?

691
00:58:46,473 --> 00:58:49,091
Now give me the knife!
Not yet!

692
00:58:51,327 --> 00:58:54,311
Ungovernable rage!

693
00:58:56,248 --> 00:58:59,388
Homicidal violence!

694
00:59:22,854 --> 00:59:25,804
Cut!
Cut and print!

695
00:59:29,649 --> 00:59:31,468
We've got it.

696
00:59:54,139 --> 00:59:56,898
Oh, not now, Ed.

697
00:59:56,921 --> 00:59:59,997
It's really not the time.

698
01:00:06,938 --> 01:00:10,491
You just can't keep this stuff
bottled up.

699
01:00:25,038 --> 01:00:28,079
Oh, God! Hitch, Hitch, you all right?

700
01:00:28,808 --> 01:00:31,506
- Can you hear me?
- Alma...

701
01:00:33,550 --> 01:00:38,593
What if Bridget and Constantine
get into the cab at the same time?

702
01:00:38,617 --> 01:00:41,658
Now what if they try and get in
at exactly the same time?

703
01:00:41,682 --> 01:00:44,176
- Yes. What do you mean, "exactly"?
- Ie reach the door...

704
01:00:44,200 --> 01:00:48,921
I mean they both reach for the cab door
at exactly the same time.

705
01:00:48,922 --> 01:00:50,587
- They quickly touch.
- Yes.

706
01:00:50,611 --> 01:00:54,075
We start on the hands,
we pan up to the eyes, and...

707
01:00:54,098 --> 01:00:56,897
Oh, that feels better already.

708
01:00:59,954 --> 01:01:02,373
- Are you going to get that?
- What?

709
01:01:28,679 --> 01:01:30,639
Listen, I've told Peggy

710
01:01:30,663 --> 01:01:34,323
you have to get this sequence
shot today.

711
01:01:34,346 --> 01:01:35,579
What's the hold-up?

712
01:01:35,603 --> 01:01:37,728
We tried it ten different ways
and it looks terrible.

713
01:01:37,745 --> 01:01:44,483
No, it has to be a high angle.
You'll tip off the big surprise.

714
01:01:44,508 --> 01:01:46,347
Just get the process shot.

715
01:01:46,675 --> 01:01:50,096
How can he hold on to the camera frame
if he's waving his arms?

716
01:01:51,101 --> 01:01:54,566
Why don't you just push all the gas
from the top of the stairs?

717
01:01:56,326 --> 01:01:57,864
No one's going to get hurt.

718
01:01:57,876 --> 01:01:59,686
What bloody idiots they are.

719
01:02:00,872 --> 01:02:02,791
- What are you doing?
- No more phone calls.

720
01:02:02,815 --> 01:02:05,269
- Oh, but...
- You're burning up.

721
01:02:05,292 --> 01:02:08,019
Burning off our money,
that's what we're doing.

722
01:02:08,042 --> 01:02:11,095
We're two days behind
and I'm stuck in this bloody bed.

723
01:02:11,118 --> 01:02:13,106
- Where do you think you're going?
- I've got to go to the set.

724
01:02:13,127 --> 01:02:18,071
- We can't lose another day.
- You stay in bed. I'll deal with it.

725
01:02:18,094 --> 01:02:22,067
I'd hate to take you away from
your writing partner.

726
01:02:23,206 --> 01:02:25,847
You stay under the blankets, Alfred.

727
01:02:31,026 --> 01:02:32,263
- Mrs. Hitchcock.
- Good morning.

728
01:02:32,286 --> 01:02:34,285
Where's Mr. Hitchcock?

729
01:02:39,727 --> 01:02:42,193
Don't stop work because of me.

730
01:02:42,216 --> 01:02:45,869
I'm only here as one of the two people
paying your salaries.

731
01:02:45,892 --> 01:02:48,578
- What's the scene number?
- 173.

732
01:02:49,978 --> 01:02:51,444
Storyboards?

733
01:02:55,372 --> 01:02:58,097
All right. Put Martin in the chair.
Turn the camera around to face him.

734
01:02:58,098 --> 01:03:01,096
We'll shoot the fall
against a rear screen.

735
01:03:01,111 --> 01:03:04,134
And, Jack, that lens should be a 35mm.

736
01:03:06,215 --> 01:03:09,066
Now, David,
you know how Paramount loves Jerry Lewis,

737
01:03:09,078 --> 01:03:10,787
but this one is right up your alley,
and I would consider...

738
01:03:10,799 --> 01:03:12,607
Barney?

739
01:03:12,618 --> 01:03:14,297
Alma!

740
01:03:14,320 --> 01:03:15,953
You know David Kirkpatrick.

741
01:03:15,970 --> 01:03:17,156
- Hello.
- Hello.

742
01:03:17,179 --> 01:03:19,510
He's working on Jerry Lewis
developing a new picture.

743
01:03:19,533 --> 01:03:21,878
So he's free to help if you need.

744
01:03:23,158 --> 01:03:24,520
That won't be necessary.

745
01:03:24,543 --> 01:03:28,378
- But you're nearly three days behind.
- Yes. Well, we can manage.

746
01:03:28,402 --> 01:03:31,715
Alma, we both know
what kind of film this is.

747
01:03:31,739 --> 01:03:35,066
The smart thing to do would be
to help Hitch finish it.

748
01:03:35,085 --> 01:03:36,711
Thank you for your concern, Barney.

749
01:03:36,735 --> 01:03:40,383
But on a Hitchcock picture,
there is only one director.

750
01:03:50,953 --> 01:03:52,870
No need to gawp.

751
01:03:59,676 --> 01:04:02,276
You forgot to look in the bathroom.

752
01:04:06,472 --> 01:04:10,111
A man like you missing
a vital clue like that...

753
01:04:12,455 --> 01:04:14,315
What do you mean?

754
01:04:17,726 --> 01:04:20,674
My mother always said

755
01:04:21,642 --> 01:04:23,986
"If you want to do a job,

756
01:04:25,937 --> 01:04:27,896
do it right."

757
01:04:40,878 --> 01:04:43,336
Check the floor.

758
01:04:46,709 --> 01:04:48,543
Closer.

759
01:05:03,913 --> 01:05:07,264
You still think they're just
writing together?

760
01:05:10,628 --> 01:05:13,257
What are you gonna do about it?

761
01:05:29,599 --> 01:05:31,402
Oh, Mrs. Hitchcock.

762
01:05:32,441 --> 01:05:36,051
I know Hitch isn't feeling very well,
so I got him a little something.

763
01:05:36,066 --> 01:05:38,918
Oh, how kind. Thank you very much.

764
01:05:39,699 --> 01:05:41,732
Candy corn.

765
01:05:41,756 --> 01:05:44,644
Well, he's always been
very considerate of me.

766
01:05:44,668 --> 01:05:47,024
I haven't always had that
from my directors.

767
01:05:49,114 --> 01:05:52,310
Janet, I'd just like to say that

768
01:05:53,670 --> 01:05:55,920
you've been very professional.

769
01:05:57,179 --> 01:05:59,520
It hasn't gone unappreciated.

770
01:06:00,766 --> 01:06:02,359
Thank you.

771
01:06:02,382 --> 01:06:04,662
- Lovely seeing you.
- You, too.

772
01:06:24,753 --> 01:06:26,867
May I turn it down?

773
01:06:34,931 --> 01:06:38,691
Well you'll be pleased to know
that order has been restored.

774
01:06:40,668 --> 01:06:42,622
And a "thank you" would be nice.

775
01:06:42,640 --> 01:06:46,170
We're still two days behind
and $60,000 over budget.

776
01:06:46,190 --> 01:06:49,442
Yes, well I'll cancel the wrap party.
That'll save us $2000 right there.

777
01:06:49,466 --> 01:06:53,626
And you won't be tempted
by any champagne and cake.

778
01:06:53,627 --> 01:06:56,730
Beware,
all men are potential murderers.

779
01:06:58,622 --> 01:07:00,786
And for good reason.

780
01:07:00,810 --> 01:07:03,610
All right, what's this all about?

781
01:07:15,370 --> 01:07:17,902
Spending a lot of time at the beach?

782
01:07:22,555 --> 01:07:24,628
Yes. Yes, it's where
Whit and I are writing.

783
01:07:24,629 --> 01:07:26,701
He's rented a place.

784
01:07:26,702 --> 01:07:30,235
Hardly the ideal situation
to avoid distractions.

785
01:07:30,236 --> 01:07:33,388
Actually, it's very conducive to
creative collaboration.

786
01:07:33,389 --> 01:07:35,890
I've already told you
that treatment is a waste of time.

787
01:07:35,913 --> 01:07:38,795
Well, didn't they say
the same thing about Psycho?

788
01:07:44,480 --> 01:07:47,205
Are you and Whit having an affair?

789
01:07:54,198 --> 01:07:56,347
Oh, don't be absurd.

790
01:07:56,371 --> 01:08:00,609
He's working on something new.
He just needs a little help, that's all.

791
01:08:00,632 --> 01:08:03,455
Oh, what a coincidence.
I'm working on something new

792
01:08:03,456 --> 01:08:05,041
and I could use a little help, too!

793
01:08:05,064 --> 01:08:06,411
Well, what do you think
I've been doing?

794
01:08:06,422 --> 01:08:08,465
Why are you spending all the hours
of day and night with that

795
01:08:08,489 --> 01:08:11,125
talentless mummy's boy?

796
01:08:12,118 --> 01:08:13,585
Because it's fun!

797
01:08:13,609 --> 01:08:16,658
I am under extraordinary pressures
on this picture,

798
01:08:16,682 --> 01:08:20,640
and the least you could do
is give me your full support.

799
01:08:20,664 --> 01:08:23,857
Full support?

800
01:08:23,881 --> 01:08:26,286
We've mortgaged our house.

801
01:08:27,666 --> 01:08:29,333
Might I remind you

802
01:08:29,357 --> 01:08:32,062
I have weighed in
on every aspect of this film so far,

803
01:08:32,086 --> 01:08:35,835
as I have done on every film
you've made in the last three decades.

804
01:08:35,859 --> 01:08:39,595
First time you show the film,
it will be my notes that you want.

805
01:08:39,618 --> 01:08:41,837
I celebrate with you
when the reviews are good.

806
01:08:41,860 --> 01:08:43,468
I cry for you when they are bad.

807
01:08:43,491 --> 01:08:47,002
I host your parties and
I put up with those fantasy romances

808
01:08:47,025 --> 01:08:49,346
with your leading ladies.

809
01:08:49,347 --> 01:08:51,623
And when you're out
promoting this film around the world,

810
01:08:51,624 --> 01:08:54,031
I will be there beside you,
or rather, slightly behind you,

811
01:08:54,054 --> 01:08:58,396
smiling endlessly for the press
even though I'm ready to drop,

812
01:08:58,419 --> 01:09:02,095
and being gracious to people who
look through me as if I were invisible

813
01:09:02,096 --> 01:09:04,399
or elbow me aside because all they can see

814
01:09:04,400 --> 01:09:08,326
is the great and glorious
genius Alfred Hitchcock!

815
01:09:08,348 --> 01:09:12,366
And now, for the first time in years,

816
01:09:12,367 --> 01:09:16,517
I dare to work on something that isn't
an Alfred Hitchcock production

817
01:09:16,518 --> 01:09:19,835
and I'm met with
accusation and criticisms?

818
01:09:21,379 --> 01:09:25,429
The work I am doing with Whit
gives me pleasure and purpose,

819
01:09:25,430 --> 01:09:29,000
and it takes absolutely
nothing away from you.

820
01:09:30,368 --> 01:09:34,664
Consider this a reminder:
I am your wife, Alma Reville.

821
01:09:34,687 --> 01:09:37,550
Not one of those contract blondes
you badger

822
01:09:37,573 --> 01:09:40,732
and torment with your
oh-so-specific directions.

823
01:10:14,998 --> 01:10:16,681
Well...

824
01:10:16,694 --> 01:10:18,812
I guess this is goodbye.

825
01:10:22,178 --> 01:10:24,632
Why didn't you stay with me?

826
01:10:26,308 --> 01:10:30,617
I would have made you
as big a star as Grace Kelly.

827
01:10:34,270 --> 01:10:37,999
Well, unlike Grace Kelly,
I can pick my own dry cleaning.

828
01:10:38,603 --> 01:10:41,286
I've got a family, Hitch. A home.

829
01:10:44,366 --> 01:10:48,187
That blonde woman of mystery
you're always after?

830
01:10:48,210 --> 01:10:50,159
She's a fantasy.

831
01:10:50,183 --> 01:10:51,852
She doesn't exist.

832
01:10:53,523 --> 01:10:56,871
There was a time when
I thought I understood you.

833
01:10:58,404 --> 01:11:00,687
Understood women.

834
01:11:52,172 --> 01:11:55,318
Alma, I thought you were coming
later this afternoon.

835
01:11:55,342 --> 01:11:57,091
I thought you rented this place
so we could write.

836
01:11:57,115 --> 01:11:58,841
I did.

837
01:12:00,375 --> 01:12:02,459
You're not going to
say anything, are you?

838
01:12:02,460 --> 01:12:04,542
Don't worry. I won't tell Elizabeth.

839
01:12:04,550 --> 01:12:07,094
I mean to Hitch.

840
01:12:08,415 --> 01:12:13,699
Alma, we can't all be geniuses.

841
01:12:13,723 --> 01:12:15,801
You're incredibly talented.

842
01:12:15,824 --> 01:12:18,917
But, after all, we want him
to read the script with an open mind.

843
01:12:18,940 --> 01:12:20,197
Don't we?

844
01:12:21,500 --> 01:12:23,766
I wouldn't worry about that, Whit.

845
01:12:28,689 --> 01:12:31,307
Sheriff, please, I'm worried.

846
01:12:31,331 --> 01:12:34,419
Arbogast said he'd call
as soon as he spoke with Mrs. Bates.

847
01:12:34,431 --> 01:12:36,485
That was yesterday evening.

848
01:12:36,509 --> 01:12:40,546
- Norman isn't married.
- He said it was his mother.

849
01:12:40,569 --> 01:12:44,366
Your detective saw Norman's mother
up at the motel?

850
01:12:44,389 --> 01:12:46,139
In the upstairs window.

851
01:12:46,150 --> 01:12:48,582
He rang me right after
she called out to him.

852
01:12:48,606 --> 01:12:52,740
Missy, I think your detective
must be a few cups in.

853
01:12:52,764 --> 01:12:59,024
Mrs. Bates died of strychnine poisoning
more than ten years ago.

854
01:12:59,047 --> 01:13:02,488
- Are you sure?
- That body was...

855
01:13:08,984 --> 01:13:12,307
This is my favorite place.

856
01:13:12,330 --> 01:13:17,987
I just shut the door
and make the world go away.

857
01:13:18,844 --> 01:13:22,419
Don't you ever get lonely out here?

858
01:13:23,800 --> 01:13:26,989
I can always talk to my mother.

859
01:13:38,769 --> 01:13:41,528
That's strange.

860
01:13:41,552 --> 01:13:44,823
Jesus Christ.
I think we found his hiding place.

861
01:13:51,263 --> 01:13:53,747
That's my mother's room.

862
01:13:54,598 --> 01:13:56,565
That's my mother's room.

863
01:14:03,365 --> 01:14:05,719
You can't go in there!

864
01:14:05,737 --> 01:14:07,778
Don't go in my mother's room!

865
01:14:21,854 --> 01:14:24,203
Hitch?

866
01:14:24,226 --> 01:14:26,152
Hitch?

867
01:14:27,244 --> 01:14:29,645
So what's the verdict?

868
01:14:29,669 --> 01:14:33,755
Let's just say it was a four-letter review
and it wasn't "good."

869
01:14:36,212 --> 01:14:37,550
Screw him.

870
01:14:37,574 --> 01:14:41,082
It's too late for Paramount to back out,
no matter what Balaban says.

871
01:14:43,191 --> 01:14:48,009
The other route is to re-cut it
as a two-parter for the TV series.

872
01:14:48,031 --> 01:14:50,299
Because of the budget
and the Hitchcock name,

873
01:14:50,311 --> 01:14:52,401
we stand a good chance
of breaking even.

874
01:14:54,667 --> 01:14:59,324
Look, I made Jimmy Stewart
a millionaire on Winchester 73,

875
01:14:59,347 --> 01:15:00,744
and that was a dog.

876
01:15:00,768 --> 01:15:03,676
At least I could sit through
your picture.

877
01:15:06,508 --> 01:15:09,982
More importantly, what does Alma think?

878
01:15:34,383 --> 01:15:36,250
I was afraid you'd try to
blame yourself.

879
01:15:36,274 --> 01:15:37,577
I'm not talking of blame.

880
01:15:37,589 --> 01:15:40,031
Leigh, how can you make plans
if you're still not sure?

881
01:15:59,958 --> 01:16:02,751
Whit must've enjoyed writing for Colbert.

882
01:16:09,393 --> 01:16:11,960
How was the beach?

883
01:16:13,643 --> 01:16:16,004
Cold and miserable.

884
01:16:17,609 --> 01:16:21,281
Just like Barney Balaban's face.

885
01:16:25,592 --> 01:16:27,848
Poor old Whit.

886
01:16:29,469 --> 01:16:33,336
He isn't worth a damn
when he's not working with you.

887
01:16:38,394 --> 01:16:40,487
Neither am I.

888
01:16:46,724 --> 01:16:50,994
I couldn't pull off the picture this time.

889
01:16:51,018 --> 01:16:54,570
It just sits there,

890
01:16:54,583 --> 01:16:57,192
refusing to come to life.

891
01:17:01,323 --> 01:17:04,717
I guess there's no other way of saying it,
is there?

892
01:17:07,011 --> 01:17:09,344
It's stillborn.

893
01:17:15,370 --> 01:17:18,028
I let you down, my love.

894
01:17:23,124 --> 01:17:25,923
You deserve better.

895
01:17:33,271 --> 01:17:35,473
Better go feed Geoffrey and Stanley.

896
01:17:37,131 --> 01:17:39,400
Come on, boys.

897
01:18:58,695 --> 01:19:01,705
I don't think I can stand us
both being maudlin.

898
01:19:02,798 --> 01:19:08,192
That tiresome little Hitchcock imitation
I've been helping Whit finish is done.

899
01:19:11,750 --> 01:19:13,957
You know there's only
one solution to all this.

900
01:19:13,981 --> 01:19:16,458
That we get back to work together.

901
01:19:17,472 --> 01:19:20,537
The fact is I rather like
living in this house.

902
01:19:20,560 --> 01:19:24,430
So I suggest, for everyone's sake,
we start whipping Psycho into shape.

903
01:19:27,356 --> 01:19:29,706
You may not be the easiest man
to live with,

904
01:19:29,717 --> 01:19:32,908
but you know how to cut a picture
better than anyone else.

905
01:19:37,489 --> 01:19:39,852
Except for you.

906
01:19:42,244 --> 01:19:45,015
The second take.
The light is much better on the hands.

907
01:19:49,089 --> 01:19:52,182
Only cut back to Janet
once the car's already moving.

908
01:19:52,194 --> 01:19:53,967
Cut it tighter.

909
01:19:57,159 --> 01:20:00,365
Ooh, you imp, you got nudity in there!

910
01:20:00,388 --> 01:20:05,457
Her breasts were rather large.
It was a challenge not to show them.

911
01:20:05,481 --> 01:20:07,221
You'll have to cut
those six or seven frames

912
01:20:07,232 --> 01:20:09,474
where she blinks after
she's supposed to be dead.

913
01:20:09,492 --> 01:20:12,863
Alma, we've viewed the film
a thousand times.

914
01:20:12,874 --> 01:20:14,671
She does not blink.

915
01:20:17,447 --> 01:20:20,888
- How's it going in there?
- Swimmingly.

916
01:20:20,910 --> 01:20:23,145
Everyone's saying it's
like a dog with fleas.

917
01:20:24,177 --> 01:20:26,220
No, absolutely not!

918
01:20:26,231 --> 01:20:29,449
I do not want music
over the show murder scene.

919
01:20:29,460 --> 01:20:31,820
But what Alma and I talked about
is really going to play.

920
01:20:31,838 --> 01:20:35,324
Bernie, this is not Vertigo.
It's not a romantic movie.

921
01:20:35,339 --> 01:20:37,121
The images must work on their own.

922
01:20:37,144 --> 01:20:39,481
Yes, but you can't scare people
just by going, "Boo!"

923
01:20:39,492 --> 01:20:41,500
All right, you do it then.
You know best.

924
01:20:41,524 --> 01:20:43,212
- They have to anticipate it.
- You always know best, just do it!

925
01:20:43,235 --> 01:20:44,752
Take a step back.

926
01:20:58,788 --> 01:21:03,037
- What do you think?
- I think I'll never have a shower again.

927
01:21:05,580 --> 01:21:08,571
- Hitch?
- It's getting there.

928
01:21:12,496 --> 01:21:15,953
I distinctly saw both
the stabbing and the nudity.

929
01:21:15,972 --> 01:21:20,658
What you think you're seeing is purely
informed by the power of suggestion.

930
01:21:20,673 --> 01:21:23,785
I assure you once you
view the final version

931
01:21:23,808 --> 01:21:26,110
with Mr. Herrmann's lovely,
lyrical score...

932
01:21:26,133 --> 01:21:30,512
A lyrical score is not going to
change my opinion.

933
01:21:31,698 --> 01:21:34,621
We're denying your seal.

934
01:21:35,526 --> 01:21:38,903
Geoffrey, would you mind if we had a word
in private, please?

935
01:21:45,411 --> 01:21:47,257
Thank you.

936
01:21:53,455 --> 01:21:55,508
Now look here.

937
01:21:55,531 --> 01:21:58,666
I have a modest proposal to make.

938
01:21:58,678 --> 01:22:02,013
If you're willing to leave
the shower sequence as it is,

939
01:22:02,036 --> 01:22:07,415
I will re-shoot the opening love scene
to your exact specifications.

940
01:22:07,439 --> 01:22:12,718
In fact, I would welcome your
personal supervision on the set.

941
01:22:16,445 --> 01:22:18,558
To my specifications?

942
01:22:18,570 --> 01:22:21,376
But of course, my dear fellow.

943
01:22:21,400 --> 01:22:24,277
If only audiences
could fully comprehend

944
01:22:24,301 --> 01:22:27,729
how tirelessly you work
to help us entertain them

945
01:22:27,753 --> 01:22:31,882
while protecting them
from filth and indecency.

946
01:22:38,646 --> 01:22:41,131
He's been harassing you
since you announced this project,

947
01:22:41,154 --> 01:22:43,550
you invite him to the set,
and he doesn't even show up?

948
01:22:43,573 --> 01:22:45,228
What did you tell him?

949
01:22:45,251 --> 01:22:48,119
That I respected him deeply.

950
01:22:51,920 --> 01:22:57,181
Ladies and gentleman, that is a wrap.
Thank you all very much.

951
01:23:00,655 --> 01:23:04,107
- I thought we were re-shooting the scene.
- The charade is over.

952
01:23:04,131 --> 01:23:05,907
Thank you.

953
01:23:11,926 --> 01:23:15,578
See, I wasn't that much of a monster
to work with, was I?

954
01:23:15,601 --> 01:23:17,280
Not at all.

955
01:23:17,304 --> 01:23:20,257
I hope I was sufficiently loyal
to the cause.

956
01:23:20,281 --> 01:23:23,183
Worthy of a Purple Heart, my dear.

957
01:23:45,485 --> 01:23:47,058
I hope you don't mind,

958
01:23:47,082 --> 01:23:50,423
I told Mrs. Bates
she could use your dressing room.

959
01:23:57,394 --> 01:24:00,850
No, that's splendid. Splendid.

960
01:24:01,739 --> 01:24:04,627
Yes, thank you.

961
01:24:05,509 --> 01:24:07,223
Thank you.

962
01:24:07,247 --> 01:24:09,897
We have the seal
from the Shurlock Office.

963
01:24:09,922 --> 01:24:12,987
So now,
we lead the lambs to the slaughter.

964
01:24:13,010 --> 01:24:16,267
Paramount confirmed they're only
opening the movie in two theaters,

965
01:24:16,291 --> 01:24:18,450
as we suspected.
And no premiere.

966
01:24:19,725 --> 01:24:22,695
We don't get word of mouth, we're dead.

967
01:24:24,287 --> 01:24:27,422
Then we'd better get started.
Peggy, take a memo.

968
01:24:27,445 --> 01:24:31,540
We're going to write a manual
on how to sell Psycho.

969
01:24:33,883 --> 01:24:36,796
"My first instruction to Theater Owners:

970
01:24:36,819 --> 01:24:42,272
Hire Pinkerton guards to strictly enforce
our unique admission policies."

971
01:24:42,296 --> 01:24:44,613
There may be riots here tonight.

972
01:24:44,614 --> 01:24:46,929
"Because is Psycho is
so terrifying and unique,

973
01:24:46,952 --> 01:24:51,664
"the guards can help you deal
with customers who run amok.

974
01:24:51,687 --> 01:24:53,588
"Post our special lobby clocks

975
01:24:53,612 --> 01:24:57,980
"to remind audiences
of the starting times for Psycho.

976
01:24:58,003 --> 01:25:02,850
The manager of this fine motion picture
theater has been advised

977
01:25:02,874 --> 01:25:07,955
not to allow anyone to enter the theater
once Psycho begins.

978
01:25:07,979 --> 01:25:12,608
Now, should you be so foolish as to
attempt to slip in by a side entrance,

979
01:25:12,631 --> 01:25:15,434
a fire escape or through a skylight,

980
01:25:15,458 --> 01:25:18,922
you will be ejected by brute force.

981
01:25:18,945 --> 01:25:21,383
More playful, darling.

982
01:25:21,406 --> 01:25:27,336
"To further emphasize the sheer,
unrelenting shock and suspense of Psycho,

983
01:25:27,359 --> 01:25:30,457
"right after the closing title "The End,"

984
01:25:30,480 --> 01:25:34,480
"we strongly recommend
that you close your house

985
01:25:34,481 --> 01:25:38,480
curtains over the screen
for a full 30 seconds.

986
01:25:39,908 --> 01:25:43,102
"By doing so, the horror of Psycho

987
01:25:43,125 --> 01:25:49,102
"will be indelibly etched
in the mind and heart of your audience.

988
01:25:49,125 --> 01:25:53,924
Sincerely and emphatically,
Alfred Hitchcock."

989
01:25:53,948 --> 01:25:56,247
Well at least there are some people here,
Hitch.

990
01:26:04,616 --> 01:26:06,536
We've roped off some seats for you.

991
01:26:07,812 --> 01:26:09,754
- You go on ahead.
- Are you sure?

992
01:26:09,773 --> 01:26:12,473
Yes, I'll be with you in a moment. I'm
just going to check the print. You go on.

993
01:26:12,497 --> 01:26:14,904
All right, darling.
We'll save you a seat, all right?

994
01:26:16,336 --> 01:26:18,345
This way, Mr. Hitchcock.

995
01:28:18,781 --> 01:28:20,584
Just got off the phone with Balaban.

996
01:28:20,607 --> 01:28:24,181
He said congratulations. A well-deserved
triumph, as we always knew.

997
01:28:24,200 --> 01:28:26,534
As we always knew, ha!

998
01:28:26,557 --> 01:28:28,674
Does this mean I can
take the weekend off now?

999
01:28:28,675 --> 01:28:30,791
Yes, dear. Thank you so much.

1000
01:28:30,815 --> 01:28:33,105
- Where's Alma?
- Go. Go on.

1001
01:28:44,566 --> 01:28:46,923
Alma, come here.

1002
01:28:53,957 --> 01:28:57,581
You know, darling, this could be the
biggest success of your career.

1003
01:28:59,061 --> 01:29:01,597
Our career.

1004
01:29:03,143 --> 01:29:10,761
Alma, I will never be able to find
a Hitchcock blonde as beautiful as you.

1005
01:29:16,040 --> 01:29:19,858
I've waited thirty years
to hear you say that.

1006
01:29:19,882 --> 01:29:26,142
And that, my dear, is why they
call me the Master of Suspense.

1007
01:29:48,516 --> 01:29:51,028
And so, gentle viewers,

1008
01:29:51,052 --> 01:29:54,828
Psycho turned out to be
one of my greatest achievements,

1009
01:29:54,851 --> 01:30:00,099
and Alma and I got to keep the house
and the swimming pool.

1010
01:30:00,122 --> 01:30:03,445
But you know what they say in Hollywood:

1011
01:30:03,469 --> 01:30:07,011
You're only as good as your last picture.

1012
01:30:07,029 --> 01:30:11,573
So if you'll excuse me,
I had better toddle away

1013
01:30:11,597 --> 01:30:16,373
to begin the exhaustive search
for my next project.

1014
01:30:16,397 --> 01:30:23,913
Unfortunately, I find myself once again
quite bereft of any inspiration.

1015
01:30:23,937 --> 01:30:29,778
However, I do hope
something comes along soon.

1016
01:30:34,548 --> 01:30:36,984
Good evening.

